item.description:
The Problem Veeam is failing to back up one of your Hyper-V VM&rsquo;s and is throwing the error: VHDx:CVhdxDisk.InitialValidation: Invalid bitmap block (all bitmap block of fixed and dynamic disks must be in SB_BLOCK_NOT_PRESENT state) Agent failed to process method {VHDx.GetDiskInformation}
The Cause The error is telling us that Veeam&rsquo;s VHDx InitialValidation function failed as the VHDx had blocks in an invalid state.
According to Microsoft&rsquo;s OpenSpecs Documentation for VHDx, the only valid Sector Bitmap Block state for fixed and dynamic disks is SB_BLOCK_NOT_PRESENT
